news.title: Pay up before May 31, property tax rebate period won’t be extended: Chandigarh civic body
news.para: The civic body has clarified that for cash and online payments, May 31 is the last date to avail of the rebate. However, those who wish to pay through cheques and demand drafts will have to do so by May 27.

news.title: RMC plants to be banned in residential areas of Ahmedabad
news.para: ​​"RMC plants in residential areas are contributing to air pollution. We are formulating a new policy, and orders for their relocation will be issued in the next two months," Dani said during the standing committee meeting on Thursday.

news.title: CBI seeks information on 24 projects in SC-ordered subvention probe
news.para: The central investigating agency has now sought details of these real estate projects — following a Supreme Court directive of April 29 — as part of a probe that involves not just gathering records from the three development authorities but also scrutinising an alleged nexus between banks and developers.

news.title: SRA invites tenders for ten slum redevelopment schemes in Mumbai
news.para: The authority has invited bids for redevelopment of ten stalled slum redevelopment schemes at Andheri West, Antop Hill in Wadala, Goregaon, Jogeshwari Vikhroli Link Road, Vikhroli, Chembur and Deonar.

news.title: Over 75 residential societies sign for redevelopment in Jan-Apr 2025
news.para: Developers say the threat of rising jantri rates in early 2025 pushed many societies to fast-track approvals. Meanwhile, recent court judgments have helped streamline the consent process — especially in cases where 75% of members are in favour, leading to fewer legal hurdles.

news.title: Pune: Case against realty firm’s three directors on charge of duping buyers in two projects
news.para: The complainant, a resident of Hinjewadi, stated that the company took money by impressing upon them that it got permission to build up to 10 floors in either project.

news.title: Land pooling policy designed to foster development: Punjab finance minister
news.para: The policy marks a significant departure from past practices, prioritising voluntary participation and empowering landowners to become active stakeholders in the state's progress, he said.

news.title: Ramco Cements' net profit dips 76% to ₹384.3 million in Q4 FY25
news.para: Adjusted net profit from the cement business sank over 76% to 384.3 million rupees ($4.5 million) in the quarter ended March 31. The company registered a one-time gain of 108.3 million rupees, tied to sale of surplus lands and investments.

news.title: Max Estates posts net profit of ₹13.99 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Sahil Vachani, vice chairman & MD of Max Estates said, "In FY25, we exceeded our full-year guidance, achieving pre-sales booking value of over ₹5,300 crore. We plan to deliver pre-sales bookings of ₹6,000-6,500 crore in FY26, a 15-20% growth over FY25."

news.title: Nearly 75% of Country Garden bondholders back offshore debt overhaul plan: Media report
news.para: Country Garden defaulted on its offshore debt in late 2023 and has since proposed to restructure its obligations by eliminating 78% of about $14.1 billion of its overall dues.

news.title: Sebi to auction 30 properties of Rose Valley group worth ₹409 crore in June 2025
news.para: ​The properties to go under the hammer include land with building, flats, resort, hotels and amusement park, buildings, plots and land parcels located in West Bengal, Andaman and Nicobar Islands, Tripura, and Bihar, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in a notice.

news.title: Century Real Estate raises ₹1,850 crore debt to fund existing and future projects
news.para: In a statement on Thursday, Bengaluru-based Century Real Estate said it has secured "Rs 1,850 crore in debt funding, led by Ares Asia and SC Lowy".

news.title: Muoro receives $3.2 million grant from Brownfield Asset Advisory for GCC expansion
news.para: Brownfield has extended a $3.2 million grant to Muoro to fast-track the development of GCCs and Centres of Excellence (COEs) in tier-II cities and North India.

news.title: Capital India Finance gets RBI approval to sell its housing finance arm
news.para: The proposed transaction is valued at ₹267 crore, for 100% equity shares of Capital India Home Loans. In October 2024, it was decided to sell its 100% stake in company’s material subsidiary.

news.title: ASK Curated Luxury Assets Fund raises ₹500 crore to invest in luxury housing projects
news.para: "This fund, aimed at investing in luxury residential projects, has evoked interest from many of India's prominent family offices, Ultra-High-Net-Worth Individuals (UHNIs), securing an investment corpus of Rs 500 crore within 3 months of its launch," ASK Property Fund said in a statement.

news.title: Fire department to engage 50 agencies to audit buildings across Telangana
news.para: Telangana has at least 5 lakh buildings that need to meet these fire safety norms. The last survey conducted by the fire dept was in 2023 when it managed to cover only 3,000 high-rises across the state.

news.title: Urban Vault leases 50,000 sq ft with at Prestige Obelisk in Bengaluru
news.para: Prestige Obelisk, developed by Prestige Group, is an 11-storey grade-A commercial building offering a total of around 1.8 lakh sq ft.

news.title: No registration of structures on rooftops: Kolkata civic body
news.para: Municipal commissioner Dhaval Jain wrote to the IG (Registration) on Tuesday, urging him to ensure that terrace properties are not registered.

news.title: Six more months for roll-out of ‘One State, One Registration’ in Maharashtra
news.para: Initially included in govt's 100-day programme, the scheme has been partially rolled out with intra-district registration launched on May 1. However, officials said after Tuesday's meeting at Mantralaya that the complex inter-district system would require additional time.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC flags rising property fraud against NRIs in Punjab
news.para: According to the court, the gravity of such acts extends far beyond individual transactions, as they corrode institutional credibility and social conscience.
